title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Suppose <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> is a field of characteristic zero. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> be a finite extension. We say <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> is a <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Root Extension</html:dfn> if there exists subfields
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}=K_{0}\subset  K_{1}\subset …\subset  K_{i}\subset  K_{i+1}\subset …\subset  K_{s}=\Bbbk ]]></fr:tex>
where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K_{i+1}=K_{i}(a_{j}^{1/n_{j}})]]></fr:tex> for some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a_{i}\in  K_{i}]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i=0,1,…,s-1]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ]]></fr:tex> is algebraic over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>, we say it can be <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Expressed by Radicals</html:dfn> if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ]]></fr:tex> lies in a root extension of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
